<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/4–2445: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>, at San Francisco</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-24">April 24,
                                    1945</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>30. We understand that Wavell is expected back in Delhi on May 1st
                                and would presumably leave London not later than the 27th.
                                Consequently, <pb facs="0263" n="251" xml:id="pg_251"/> if you
                                desire to speak to Eden along the lines of Phillips’ suggestion, it
                                would have to be done now, otherwise the opportunity will be
                                lost.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>